storyInfo: The colonel thanks Horn for helping him find the Dublinn-supporting rabble, while committing acts of indiscriminate military terror upon Taran homes in order to root out Mandragora. As the mood stretches wire-thin, the ballroom abruptly suffers a bombing attack.

attributes.content: Colonel.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: We meet again, Skamandros.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: You don't seem one bit surprised.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Surprised?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: No, from the first I met you, I have not been one bit surprised—you were bound to mingle with this rabble, simply because of that cheap sympathy you learned from your noble etiquette classes.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: You shadowed us?!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: I'd rather term this rational management.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Regardless of anything, I must thank you. If it weren't for your leading the way, I wouldn't have such a sublime opportunity to net all these rot-eating vermin in one fell swoop.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: You hide fairly deep most of the time, don't you?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: I confess I'm quite curious. What made you so audacious as to gather up? Could it be that from the outcomes of your last few pathetic, negligible sneak attacks, you mistakenly believed County Hillock was already under your control?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: A-Ahem... Colonel, sir, I believe there may be some misunderstanding at play here.
attributes.name: Wildly Ambitious Baron

attributes.content: That is wrong, Baron Bolton. There is no misunderstanding between us whatsoever. I am pristinely clear about your confidential lowly dealings.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: It's only some of my good friends and family gathered here today. That, I can guarantee you on my very name—
attributes.name: Wildly Ambitious Baron

attributes.content: Shut up kindly, good sir. The honor you've inherited from your ancestry purchases nothing in my eyes.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Y—You have some nerve saying that!
attributes.name: Pretentious Noblewoman

attributes.content: The one dishonoring your so-called noble reputation isn't me by far. Who are they, reveling in the position and wealth Victoria accords them, then turning to secretly collude with the most lowly rebels of them all?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: This is out-and-out slander!
attributes.name: Pretentious Noblewoman

attributes.content: I'm starting to be sick of this blather now. You rabble should behave as the rabble outside, weeping in the light of a blaze while you confess your own wrongdoings.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Just as he said, from outside the window come wails and cries, the glass reflecting speckled points of fire.
(Leader, look outside! It's not just in here, he's got the Tarans from the whole block surrounded too.)
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: (He's not exaggeratin' at all. He's cowerin' ordinary residents with military force.)
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: (I've been around that street before—a huge portion of them are elderly and children!)
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: (With methods suddenly this radical, it seems there's some other information he has a hold on. He's very likely to have hidden intel about the spectre force from us.)
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: (Nothin' from Triangle?)
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: (No comms at all since afternoon.)
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: (Flip. Could somethin' have happened to them?)
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: (There's no point in worrying. What's more pressing right now is we should hold the troops back as much as we can.)
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: (We can't stay trapped in here, at least...)
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: You, the Vouivre over there. You are not to think of breaking out through the wall. Before my questioning bears fruit, no one is allowed to leave this room.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Ugh, he spotted me!
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Come out! I see you! No movement, I want you to kneel here and behave!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Agh!
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: Is there anyone else in your home? Speak up!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: N—No...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: You're not hiding anyone? I'll see for myself. Listen, so long as I see you move a muscle, no matter what you're trying at, I will immediately shoot your head through.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: *Whimper*...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: What are you doing?!
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Who are you, coming from nowhere and running in front of my crossbow? Watch your own head!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Wait, hold on, I recognize you. You're that guard of honor from Adams's group, aren't you? I saw you at the New Year do. Your group didn't get any order to move. What are you doing here?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: I have another assignment nearby I'm on.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Fine, then, each to their own. Don't you start getting in my way.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: (That lass called Bagpipe told me I could step forth too, change the situation.)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (Can I, though...? I have to try, at least...)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Did they... do something wrong, to be treated this rough?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: You're asking me? Why don't you go ask them?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: What are you crying for? Wasn't it you lot, harboring thugs, giving them food and drink, feeding them information?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Do you have evidence?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Evidence? You want evidence? Do the wounds on the 9th and 13th count? Each one of their bodies still warm?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Some died by eerie Originium Arts, some died by makes of crossbows and sabers identical to the ones we carry, and some had traces on their necks left behind by farming tools.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Our heads cut off with threshers like wheat, bodies crushed thin and flat by tractors like plowed land—have you ever... pictured that? The devastation?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Ulp...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: That's right, you should want to puke. I saw with my own eyes, and I recognized who that head used to belong to, and for an entire afternoon, I puked. I couldn't stop.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: They... why would they treat their own like this... this is too cruel!
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Hah, damn right you are. Behaving never suited them.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Now you understand this serves them right, don't you?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: What are you still blanking out for?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: So... these are all bad people? Just because... they're all Tarans?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: *Sob*... agh... I haven't done a thing, Sir...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: She's crying.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Her husband already passed away from Oripathy, and her child's only pushing ten... is someone bereft like this really going to be a murderer?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: How have I not gotten it through to you?! They're all one kind, do you understand? Even if this woman and her child haven't done anything yet, they're all together in this.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: If it wasn't a Taran, in front of you all, but some other Victorian citizen...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Would you still insist on treating them all as thugs?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: If... I'm just saying, if, from the very beginning, there were never those discriminatory laws, if Tarans could've earned as much as anyone else, gotten the same chance at healthcare...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Wouldn't none of this conflict have ever happened?!
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Alright, guard of honor, if you love asking questions so much, keep asking. There won't be an answer. Nobody's got any way of answering you. I'm essentially done searching this house by now anyway, so it's onto the next one.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Hey! I said I was going, not that you could stand up!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: *Sob*... Ah... don't take me, Craig can't be without me...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: Shut it with all the sobbing! Wailing about your child all day long just so I can go soft on you, is it?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Just let her go.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Eugh, you. Fine, I'm busy anyway. I can afford to ignore this woman.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: But just to warn you, you might be protecting them now with all your kind heart, but be careful they don't blow you sky-high without blinking the moment your head is turned.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Don't you forget, after all, you and them aren't the same kind. Have you seen the looks in their eyes before? In their eyes, no matter how you behave, you'll always be one of us.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Just go... Please.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: *spits* Don't say I didn't warn you.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Phew... you've not been harmed, no?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (Shakes head)
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: It's lucky. After me and Saoirse talked, I couldn't shake this nervous feeling, and I had to come back and take a look.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: So it really can be a bit of use... to stand up.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Come on, I'll help you back inside. For tonight... no, tomorrow as well, don't go out, please. There's ruffians outside, as well as... um, at any rate, Hillock won't be as safe for these next few days.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Right, and where's your boy...? Craig? He's not at home?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Craig... he... *gulp*...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: He's been taken away by the soldiers, hasn't he?!
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I... I don't know...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: I need to go and find him.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Hill!
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Colonel, we've just apprehended this one in this corridor outside, right as he was attempting to dive out of the window.
attributes.name: Adjutant Hill

attributes.content: I'm sorry, I'm sorry...
attributes.name: Frightened Youth

attributes.content: Let me guess, this boy is some follower of yours, preparing to send word to somebody or other?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: I... (Wipes off a cold sweat)
attributes.name: Wildly Ambitious Baron

attributes.content: I want a lawyer! I know the Mayor and quite a few Members too... Let me go, you have no authority to keep us held like this!
attributes.name: Greedy Businessman

attributes.content: It seems my guess was dead on. Every one of you has some involvement.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: You may speak. All I need to know is where your co-conspirators are hiding.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: How about this, then. I'll count to three—
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Aaaargh! Don't, don't kill me!
attributes.name: Frightened Youth

attributes.content: My goodness... Why must you have me see such cruelty?
attributes.name: Pretentious Noblewoman

attributes.content: You can't be doin' this!
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Really? Skamandros, tell your subordinate, do I have the right to be doing this?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Leader...!
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Provisional administrative law... In the event we are unable to receive direct orders from Londinium, Colonel Hamilton is the highest acting commander of the County Hillock barracks, and does possess the authority to impose martial law on the whole city.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: I know! But if he's seriously goin' to do this, then he's essentially declarin' a formal war on the hidden army!
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: I fear that one thing they've said is right. We are already situated within in a war.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: But we barely know more than nothin' about that army.
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: We're stark open and they're still in the shadows. No matter what, I don't feel now was good timin' to open fire first.
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Timing! They never picked any timing when they launched attacks on us unilaterally.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Colonel, even if you won't take any suggestion from our team, I still must express clear opposition to the course of action you are about to adopt.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Very thankful for your one scrap of self-awareness shown.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: In honesty, I'm not fond of doing this either. As long as they'd left me another choice, I would never be willing to break the Empire's laws.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Yet we're out of time. The hidden enemy is closing in with each step.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Isn't this as you said too, Skamandros? You, too, came to drag the ghosts out into the sunlight!
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: If we don't seize this opportunity, and force all the remaining conspirators out, then we will have lost County Hillock before the morrow.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Colonel, I believe the more critical the juncture, the more each step we choose will lead to divergent results.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: I'm sure, there are many innocents among those present. You can take them away first, and then...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: No, I have no time to squander on pointless interrogation. Right now, on this very spot, these rabblesome dregs will make clear where in the world their members are hidden!
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Hill, do it! We've tarried for long enough—
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: ...Colonel.
attributes.name: Bard Williams

attributes.content: And who in Hell's bloody bells are you?
attributes.name: Hamilton

attributes.content: Please arrest me. I am Baron Bolton's guest, and will know much more than any of these poor young people, rendered near-unconscious.
attributes.name: Bard Williams

attributes.content: Seamus! What are you doing stepping up?
attributes.name: Wildly Ambitious Baron

attributes.content: Seamus... Seamus Williams. You're that bard?
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: I am, Colonel.
attributes.name: Bard Williams

attributes.content: Very good. I'd been meaning to look for you, so as to keep you from continuing to incite those imbeciles with your blither.
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: Williams...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You need not fear, ma'am. I ought to thank the Colonel, for just a moment ago, I worked out how my poem should conclude.
attributes.name: Bard Williams

attributes.content: Seize him!
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: A... ball? Where have I seen this...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Hill! Order those posted outside to find the rabble who broke that window...
attributes.name: Colonel Hamilton

attributes.content: No, this isn't right.
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: There's a sound... comin' from the ball!
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Get down!!!
attributes.name: Bagpipe

attributes.content: Who—Who was that? Where did you show up from?!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Argh—! It's—It's you lot! G—Go inform the Colonel double-time, 4th has run into the thugs, in an alley by the square—
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: This group has been annihilated.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Leader, the nearby Taran blocks have all been occupied by ours.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: You lot are...
attributes.name: Wounded Youth

attributes.content: It—It's you?! You're the... the one we've been waiting for!
attributes.name: Wounded Youth

attributes.content: You actually gave your hand to me... I...
attributes.name: Wounded Youth

attributes.content: There'll be no one else to oppress you again.
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: And you'll never need anyone's arm to lean on again.
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: From this moment on, you can walk freely upon this soil, by your own power.
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: Thank you... oh, thank you! Everything I did, it really was right!
attributes.name: Wounded Youth

attributes.content: There'll be a day for us Tarans... when we can have our own city, we can walk heads held high in the streets, we'll never be given injust treatment again!
attributes.name: Wounded Youth

attributes.content: Yes. It is precisely for that day that we come.
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: Leader, you have to see! It's—It's the fire we lit in your service!
attributes.name: Wounded Youth

attributes.content: The ballroom...
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: According to the report Madam Mandragora gave, the barracks' top brass are all in there.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: However, an explosion of that scale would only give the barracks' arrogance pause. Unfortunately, it could never wipe them out.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Apart from the barracks, who else is there?
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: Some locals who will us well. They learned of some of our inside matters, and the heads' thoughts are, for the overall picture, we can't leave anyone alive to tell tales.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: They also said, if you won't make a move, they will themselves.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: ...In the end... my fire is quicker.
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: Tell them, I know what should be done—
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: I'll take the ballroom.
attributes.name: 'The Leader

attributes.content: Yes, Leader—your fire will break these shackles that have chained us for centuries!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier
